  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "As a user I want to be able to see if the number of unread or new messages in a chat make it worthwhile to open the chat to read up on messages or ignore them in case there are too many.\r\n\r\nThe current logic and representation of unread/new messages is not achieving the goal. Often all chats are shown to have +9 messages and it is not clear how to get rid of this indicator; As a result it continues to draw attention and causes a lot of frustration.\r\n\r\nWhile we look for smarter solutions to display and interact with unread/new messages, we want to introduce this quick fix to help people decide whether a chat is worthwhile opening.\r\n\r\n### Current\r\nTheChat list shows the number of unread/new messages in a blue circle, if the number of messages is >9, it is displayed as +9.\r\n\r\n### Expected\r\n- The chat list shows the number of unread/new messages in a blue circle. If the number of messages is >99, it is displayed as +99,\r\n- The bubble should grow horizontally to accommodate the number with sufficient padding of 6 on both sides\r\n\r\n[Link to Figma](https://www.figma.com/file/aS1ct66VQ6V0cio7vSqS8UoG/Chat?node-id=5332%3A27331)\r\n\r\n<img width=\"375\" alt=\"Home Tab\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/66902879-bb542c00-f001-11e9-8af1-5a0f5e74e0d8.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
